# Testing & Quality Assurance Rules for Claude

Extend the existing testing conventions with Claude-specific guidelines for comprehensive test coverage and quality.

## Test Creation Requirements

### When Writing Tests
- **ALWAYS** create tests for new components
- **ALWAYS** use existing testing utilities from `~/unit-test-utils/`
- **FOLLOW** the `.spec.tsx` naming convention
- **PLACE** tests in `__tests__/` directories within component folders

### Test File Structure
```tsx
import { render, screen, fireEvent } from '@testing-library/react';
import { SystemNotificationConfig } from '~/types/notification-type';
import { NotificationHeader } from '../NotificationHeader';

describe('NotificationHeader', () => {
  const mockOnClose = jest.fn();

  beforeEach(() => {
    jest.clearAllMocks();
  });

  it('renders with empty notifications', () => {
    render(<NotificationHeader onClose={mockOnClose} notifications={[]} />);
    expect(screen.getByText('0 total, 0 new (past hour)')).toBeInTheDocument();
  });
});
```

## Testing Patterns to Follow

### Mock Strategies
```tsx
// ✅ Use existing mock utilities
import { createK8sWatchResourceMock } from '~/unit-test-utils/mock-k8s';
import { renderWithQueryClientAndRouter } from '~/unit-test-utils/rendering-utils';

// ✅ Mock child components when testing integration
jest.mock('../NotificationItem', () => ({
  NotificationItem: ({ title, summary }: { title: string; summary: string }) => (
    <div data-testid="notification-item">{title}: {summary}</div>
  ),
}));
```

### Time and Date Testing
```tsx
// ✅ Use fake timers for consistent time-based tests
beforeAll(() => {
  jest.useFakeTimers();
  jest.setSystemTime(new Date('2024-01-01T12:00:00Z'));
});

afterAll(() => {
  jest.useRealTimers();
});
```

### User Interaction Testing
```tsx
// ✅ Test user interactions with userEvent
import userEvent from '@testing-library/user-event';

it('calls onClose when close button is clicked', async () => {
  const user = userEvent.setup();
  render(<NotificationHeader onClose={mockOnClose} notifications={[]} />);
  
  await user.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /close/i }));
  expect(mockOnClose).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);
});
```

## Quality Checks

### Before Committing
- **RUN** `npm run type-checks` to verify TypeScript
- **RUN** `npm run lint` to check code style
- **RUN** `npm test` for relevant test files
- **VERIFY** tests pass and coverage is maintained

### Code Review Readiness
- Components have proper TypeScript interfaces
- Error states are handled appropriately
- Loading states use PatternFly Spinner in Bullseye
- Accessibility attributes are present (aria-labels, roles)

## Test Coverage Goals

### Component Testing
- **Props validation**: Test all prop combinations
- **State changes**: Test user interactions and state updates
- **Error handling**: Test error and loading states
- **Edge cases**: Test empty states, boundary conditions

### Integration Testing
- **Parent-child communication**: Test prop passing and callbacks
- **Context usage**: Test components that use React context
- **Route integration**: Test components that use routing

## Mock Data Patterns

### Creating Test Data
```tsx
// ✅ Create reusable mock factories
const createMockNotification = (overrides: Partial<SystemNotificationConfig> = {}): SystemNotificationConfig => ({
  component: 'test-component',
  title: 'Test Notification',
  type: 'info',
  summary: 'Test summary',
  created: new Date().toISOString(),
  ...overrides,
});

// ✅ Use in tests
const notifications = [
  createMockNotification({ title: 'First Notification' }),
  createMockNotification({ title: 'Second Notification' }),
];
```

### Time-based Testing
```tsx
// ✅ Test time-sensitive functionality
it('calculates recent notifications correctly', () => {
  const now = new Date();
  const thirtyMinutesAgo = new Date(now.getTime() - 30 * 60 * 1000);
  const twoHoursAgo = new Date(now.getTime() - 2 * 60 * 60 * 1000);
  
  const notifications = [
    createMockNotification({ created: thirtyMinutesAgo.toISOString() }),
    createMockNotification({ created: twoHoursAgo.toISOString() }),
  ];

  render(<NotificationHeader onClose={jest.fn()} notifications={notifications} />);
  expect(screen.getByText('2 total, 1 new (past hour)')).toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

## Performance Testing

### Component Performance
- Test components with large datasets
- Verify loading states don't block UI
- Test responsive behavior at different screen sizes

### Test Performance
- Keep test suites fast (< 10 seconds per file)
- Use selective mocking to avoid unnecessary setup
- Group related tests in describe blocks

These testing rules ensure high-quality, maintainable tests that complement the existing testing infrastructure.